  "body": "Private transactions have read access to the public state.\n\nPrivate transactions can call public contracts (which in turn can call other public contracts, etc). We encountered a bug, where a private transaction called a public transaction, which called another public transaction, where the transaction failed (https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/2816).\n\nWe need to investigate whether there are other problems similar to this, where public contracts are called.\n",
